FT  26 FEB 92 / UK Company News: Cookson sells two offshoots for Pounds 7.5m
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Cookson Group, the industrial materials company, is selling two wholly-owned
subsidiaries to the US-based Titanium Industries for about Pounds 7.5m.
Combined net assets of the two offshoots - Titanium International and
Reactive Metal Fabricators (Anston) - at December 31 amounted to
approximately Pounds 2.6m. They incurred pre-tax losses of Pounds 164,000 on
sales of Pounds 10.8m over the year to that date.
