<HEADLINE>
FT  26 FEB 92 / UK Company News: B'ham Midshires falls 40% to Pounds 9.5m
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Pre-tax profits at Birmingham Midshires, the building society, dropped by 40
per cent last year after loan loss provisions of Pounds 36.6m. Profits for
1991 were down from Pounds 15.9m to Pounds 9.5m. Bad debt provisions in 1990
were Pounds 13.5m.
During the year the society repossessed 1,542 homes, proportionately double
the average for the industry size.
Total assets rose from Pounds 3.65bn to Pounds 3.74bn and reserves by Pounds
6.1m to Pounds 143.1m.
