<HEADLINE>
FT  26 FEB 92 / Irish Sea gas field project approved
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By JULIET SYCHRAVA
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
BRITISH GAS yesterday received official permission from the Department of
Energy to develop its North Morecambe gas field in the Irish Sea, Juliet
Sychrava writes.
The field is about 25 miles off the Lancashire coast close to the larger
South Morecambe field. It will produce at a rate of 588m cu ft a day, or
about 5 per cent of UK gas consumption, and is expected to start output in
October 1994.
British Gas has already started work on a new Pounds 295m terminal to handle
the gas, next to its existing terminal at Barrow-in-Furness. The total value
of the project is estimated at just more than Pounds 500m.
</TEXT>
