square, has also been called in by Mr Heseltine.
Mr Heseltine has called on the landowners and the corporation to prepare a
master plan to guide development. 'In my view it is essential that this area
is developed in a coherent way and to the highest possible standards, given
the national importance of the site.'
He added that he would consider the called-in planning applications on their
merits. 'However, they will be judged against the high standards I consider
to be appropriate for this site and the need for the area to be developed
coherently.'
