spokesman, said.
Mr Chung initially refused to pay Won136.1bn (Pounds 101.8m) in penalty
taxes but later changed his mind. Since then, domestic banks have frozen
fresh loans to the group, the tax office has launched a second tax
investigation and the Securities Supervisory Board has postponed approval on
Hyundai units' rights issues for the sixth time, Hyundai officials said.
