formerly a bank; another was a chapel. They are run on traditional lines,
offering a wide range of real ales and a music-free environment.
All of the pubs offer one beer at 99p a pint compared with the national
average of 134p. The company has invested Pounds 6m in seven new outlets
during the past six months and plans to open another five pubs in the next
two months.
