<HEADLINE>
FT  26 FEB 92 / Top-of-range private medical plan launched
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ALAN PIKE, Social Affairs Correspondent
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
NORWICH Union Healthcare yesterday launched a top-of-the-range private
medical insurance scheme which will eliminate the need for most clients to
use the National Health Service.
The Premier Care policy will be marketed by Norwich Union for 'people who do
not want to rely on the NHS.'
Treatment for a number of conditions and procedures which are excluded from
many private medical insurance schemes - among them infertility, long-term
renal dialysis and pregnancy - will be covered. It will also pay for
consultations with private GPs and include private dental treatment and eye
tests.
The Premier Care policy will be aimed at individuals willing to pay a
higher-than-average premium to side-step the NHS in most eventualities.
The cost of the new policy will depend on age and medical history, with a
healthy 35-year-old paying about Pounds 1,000 a year. Most pre-existing
conditions will be taken on for a higher premium.
