<HEADLINE>
FT  25 FEB 92 / Letter: More a grande dame than a woman down at heel
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   From Dr HELENE SEPPAIN
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Sir, Joe Rogaly, in his column 'Beurre Heseltine' (February 21), describes
Mrs Margaret Thatcher as 'She who regarded herself as the sole bonne femme'.
I cannot believe this to be true. Une bonne femme denotes a total lack of
sophistication, namely a woman down at heel and rather vulgar.
Mrs Thatcher may well have seen herself as the sole grande dame as she
assumed the airs of an absolutist monarch. I suggest that He who regards
himself as un homme du monde should first check his French.
Helene Seppain,
174 Huntingdon Road,
Cambridge CB3 0LB
</TEXT>
